cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper proposes a multi-task learning framework for modeling and predicting a set of temporal events in the context of intelligent transportation systems. The proposed framework uses support vector regression for joint learning of mutually dependent time series. The paper also discusses the relatedness of observed time series and proposes a method to align multiple time series by inferring their common latent representation. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper proposes a novel machine learning framework for time series prediction. Additionally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely as the paper deals with the problem of travel demand prediction in a public transport system, which involves analyzing social and information networks and using data structures and algorithms to model and predict travel demand.
